-- Mexico Stocks: Banorte, Grupo Elektra Advance; Mexichem Falls
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2011-12-23T18:35:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-23/mexico-stocks-banorte-grupo-elektra-advance-mexichem-falls.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:25 p.m. in Mexico City.  The IPC  index (MEXBOL)  rose 0.2 percent to 37,150.66.  Retail and banking: Orders for U.S. durable goods rose in
November by 3.8 percent, the most in four months, and more than
the 2.2 percent economists had predicted, data from the Commerce
Department showed today in Washington.  Grupo Financiero Banorte SAB (GFNORTEO)  , Mexico’s third-
largest bank by outstanding loans, rose 0.8 percent to 43.55
pesos.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire Ricardo Salinas, gained 0.6
percent to 1,409.99 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, gained 0.3 percent to 38.09 pesos. Copper
futures for March delivery rose as much as 1.9 percent in New
York.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM*)  , Latin America’s biggest maker
of plastic pipes, fell 1.3 percent to 44.49 pesos. Mexichem
raised its bid to 508 million euros ($663 million) for Wavin NV,
Europe’s biggest maker of plastic pipes for sewers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
